column5: Thought I would share the last five minutes of my half hour laker fight on here for everyone. I was targeting walleyes with this light rig I had on. Best hard water fight of my life. You may be able to tell that I was a bit excited. After ten minutes of holding the fish in the hole, it gave me a strong tail kick and swam away well. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7Ypyp5dY4v8
Hooked right through the tip of the snout, eh! Nicely Done
Nice Catch!! Beautiful fish. Glad to hear she is still swimming too. _______________
Amazing lake trout Colin !!!.....very jealous right now..can't wait to be up in July, see you then!!!!Eric
What a beautiful fish. Congrats and good on you for putting her back.
